<subSubSection box="[619,968,264,291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="4.[619,968,264,291]" box="[619,968,264,291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading box="[619,968,264,291]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="2">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Risso, 1826" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[702,968,264,291]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Dentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[702,823,264,291]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Dentalina</emphasis>
Risso, 1826
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,310,330,356]" box="[189,310,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,330,356]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,377,579]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Elongate, arcuate, uniserial tests; chambers cylindrical to ovate, sutures oblique; wall calcareous, hyaline radial in structure; aperture terminal and radiate. The generic distinction (
<bibRefCitation author="Loeblich A. R. &amp; Tappan H." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="239 - 265" refId="ref64216" refString="Loeblich A. R. &amp; Tappan H. 1986. Some new and revised genera and families of hyaline calcareous Foraminiferida (Protozoa). Transactions of the American Microscopical Society 105 (3): 239 - 265. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3226297" type="journal article" year="1986">Loeblich &amp; Tappan 1986</bibRefCitation>
) between species with a smooth surface of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loeblich &amp; Tappan" authorityYear="1986" box="[773,949,447,473]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Laevidentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[773,949,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Laevidentalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a costate exterior of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[1254,1371,447,473]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Dentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1254,1371,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Dentalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not used here, following 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayward B. W. &amp; Kawagata S. &amp; Sabaa A. &amp; Grenfell H. &amp; Van Kerckhoven L. &amp; Johnson K. &amp; Thomas E." box="[486,799,482,509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="408" refId="ref63648" refString="Hayward B. W., Kawagata S., Sabaa A., Grenfell H., Van Kerckhoven L., Johnson K. &amp; Thomas E. 2012. The last global extinction (Mid-Pleistocene) of deep-sea benthic foraminifera (Chrysalogoniidae, Ellipsoidinidae, Glandulonodosariidae, Plectofrondiculariidae, Pleursostomellidae, Stilostomellidae), their Late Cretaceous-Cenozoic history and taxonomy. Cushman Foundation for Foraminiferal Research Special Publication 43: 408." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hayward 
<emphasis box="[601,660,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
(2012: 109
</bibRefCitation>
, 236). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[882,999,482,508]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Dentalina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[882,999,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Dentalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1816" box="[1156,1280,482,508]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Nodosaria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1156,1280,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nodosaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having more oblique than horizontal sutures, and test shape is more arcuate than straight, and more cylindrical than nodular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
